<p class="article-lead">Compare perfume manufacturers with one written brief and one evidence checklist. Otherwise each supplier prices a different product and the lowest quotation wins only because it excludes more work.</p><h2>Normalize the offer</h2><p>Use the same concentration, bottle size, quantity, decoration, carton, inspection scope and Incoterm. Separate tooling and setup from recurring unit costs. Record what remains unconfirmed.</p><h2>Verify capability</h2><p>Ask who performs formulation, compounding, filling, decoration and export. Review real production media, sample quality, approval records and defect handling. A factory visit or live walkthrough should match the legal entity and process in the quotation.</p><p>Score communication too: a supplier that identifies compatibility, compliance or logistics risks before payment is often safer than one promising every requirement immediately.</p>
